buffer are reached.
!Topic 129 Log File Toggle (Alt-0)

Qmodem activity can be recorded in a disk file with the LOG File feature. 
Events such as: FON Entries called, time and duration of call, are just a few
of the things recorded in the Log file.  

Each Log entry is Time and Date stamped.   If the Log file is closed, a
prompt will be issued to override the default Log file name and start
recording.  If Log recording is active, the recording will stop and the Log
file will be closed.

