!Topic 120 Backspace <> DEL Toggle (Alt-1)

The Backspace key can be programmed to send either the IBM-PC standard ^H
character (hex 08), or it can send the VT100 standard DEL character (hex
7F).  While online, if your Backspace key does not seem to function
correctly, try toggling this.

NOTE: Holding down the Ctrl key and pressing Backspace will generate the
opposite code.
!Topic 121 Video 25-Line Mode (Alt-2)

If you have an EGA, or greater video card, this will switch the screen into
80x25 mode.  You may want this in case you use the Alt-4 command and decide
it is not as readable.

It should be noted, that you are not limited to just Alt-2 and Alt-4.  If
your video card supports SuperEGA or SuperVGA and can be programmed into one
of a dozen different display modes, just do it before starting up Qmodem! 
The current video mode detected at startup will be used automatically!
